: both; text-align: left;\"><a style=\"clear: left; float: left; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0045.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0045-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" border=\"0\" /></a><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0047.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0047-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" border=\"0\" /></a><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0046.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0046-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"133\" border=\"0\" /></a><a style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;\" href=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0044.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/dsc_0044-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"133\" height=\"200\" border=\"0\" /></a></div>','And He\'s Off!','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2015-11-10 21:19:55','2015-11-10 21:19:55','',10,'http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/?p=42',0,'revision','',0),(43,1,'2015-11-10 21:20:46','2015-11-10 21:20:46','<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px;\">I love getting e-mail, and thank you all for sending it to me, but I only have the opportunity to check that on p-day (which is Thursdays for now). While I\'m in the MTC there is a service that will print letters and deliver them. With the subject line of \"Elder Andrew Finlayson\" you can send letters to letter@mtcmexicocarepackage.com.  For now I just steal Elder Andersen\'s letters from his family, he thinks it is funny.  I have bonded with Elder Andersen we are best friends!</p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">My first week was hard. My companion, Elder Jones is from Idaho, and our roommates are from Mexico. I am able to have small conversations and was able to co<span style=\"display: inline;\">mmit an \"investigator\" to baptism. Mission prep was so wonderful, but there is so much that I want to teach, but don\'t know how to say it in Spanish. I suppose that will come.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">We have 4 missionaries in our district from the US that will be going to Culiacan together.  I love being with the other missionaries.  I have made wonderful friends already, and excited to be able to go into the mission field with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; display: inline; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px;\">Please continue to pray for me as I study Spanish, that I will be able to pick up the language quickly. Please pray that I will have patience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">Love you all\r\nElder Finlayson</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','\"There is lots and lots of Spanish here!\"','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-10 21:20:46','2015-11-10 21:20:46','',9,'http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/?p=43',0,'revision','',0),(44,1,'2015-11-10 21:20:54','2015-11-10 21:20:54','<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px;\">I love getting e-mail, and thank you all for sending it to me, but I only have the opportunity to check that on p-day (which is Thursdays for now). While I\'m in the MTC there is a service that will print letters and deliver them. With the subject line of \"Elder Andrew Finlayson\" you can send letters to letter@mtcmexicocarepackage.com.  For now I just steal Elder Andersen\'s letters from his family, he thinks it is funny.  I have bonded with Elder Andersen we are best friends!</p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">My first week was hard. My companion, Elder Jones is from Idaho, and our roommates are from Mexico. I am able to have small conversations and was able to co<span style=\"display: inline;\">mmit an \"investigator\" to baptism. Mission prep was so wonderful, but there is so much that I want to teach, but don\'t know how to say it in Spanish. I suppose that will come.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px; margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">We have 4 missionaries in our district from the US that will be going to Culiacan together.  I love being with the other missionaries.  I have made wonderful friends already, and excited to be able to go into the mission field with them.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: white; color: #141823; display: inline; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 19.32px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px;\">Please continue to pray for me as I study Spanish, that I will be able to pick up the language quickly. Please pray that I will have patience.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px; margin-top: 6px;\">Love you all\r\nElder Finlayson</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','\"There is lots and lots of Spanish here!\"','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2015-11-10 21:20:54','2015-11-10 21:20:54','',9,'http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/?p=44',0,'revision','',0),(45,1,'2015-11-10 21:21:20','2015-11-10 21:21:20','<img style=\"float: left; height: 320px; width: 256px;\" src=\"http://ke5zwg.webhop.me/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/received_102038167503785161-240x300.jpeg\" alt=\"\" hspace=\"10\" />      The learning is coming along and I am starting to understand more and more.  It was so great to get so many emails and letters this week.  I still have to work hard but talking with the native missionaries is helping a lot, they are very patient and helpful.\r\n\r\nFor recreation we play lots of ping pong and volleyball.  I have been loosing some weight so I need to go and see the CCM doctor this week, but not to worry, I had some to spare. The food is getting better as my standards are getting lower!\r\n\r\nI have been singing in the choir, it is all in Spanish so that is helping also with learning more and more.  I spoke in our branch this week as well, it was kinda hard, but you know I killed it!\r\n\r\nThis week we got to leave the CCM compound and go to the Mexico City Temple it was so nice to be out and seeing the city.  I loved the temple and being able to go.  Part of the session was in English and part in Spanish so that was awesome.\r\n\r\nWell I have a hard time understanding what people are saying and with reading right now and as we went in to meet with our first investigator I said a prayer a really hard prayer and I went into the room and as she began to speak to us, really fast by the way. I understood, not translated to English understood, I just knew what she was saying and started to talk back with her in Spanish.  I don\'t remember what I said but I could feel the spirit so strong and then I read her Helaman 10:5 which is so long in Spanish and i didn\'t have any problems it was a true miracle.\r\n\r\nI love getting letters so keep them coming, it helps keep my spirits up.  I have sent some pictures.  Love you all very much.\r\nyo se la expacion es por todal personas y la amor de Dios en infenyado. yo amor mí family mucho mas\r\n<div><img class=\"\" src=\"https://lh3.goog