ders oh and we didn\'t have water today.\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-107\" src=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/pn_zone_chill-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Chillin with zone leaders\" width=\"325\" height=\"183\" /> <a href=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/pn_zone_splits.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-108\" src=\"http://www.elderfinlayson.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/pn_zone_splits-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Zone leaders with us on bikes\" width=\"326\" height=\"183\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tuesday</strong>: today was alright we had an less active who we had a plan to see and we went to his house and he was smoking a lot of weed because his wife left him and i really feel bad for him. also this morning was district meeting and we practiced a special musical number we are singing for multi zone this Friday so crazy how time fly\'s!\r\n\r\nIf you thought it was Wednesday  you were wrong lol time to feel the spirit! one of the only things that keeps me going out here is my personal study so i am going to add some of these to put on my blog.  I pray before I do these special study\'s for the things that  the people who read my blog will need so this is the first one for this week:\r\n<blockquote>FORGIVENESS - forgiveness is like a coin it has 2 parts 2 sides we can use: the perfect everlasting atonement of Christ, and the need to forgive others. Our life is like a hiking trail when we start out we are clean but as we sin Satan begins to put some rocks in our backpack.  But as we are baptized we get a new backpack no rocks, but because we are human we still sin. As we sin Satan still puts rocks in our backpack but as we exercise the atonement, the receiving of forgiveness for our sins, Christ walks behinds us and takes rocks out.\r\nNow is the other part of the coin your forgiveness of others.   Someone else sins, they wronged you and you get upset and take offense, now the grater sin is on you (<a href=\"https://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/64.9,10?lang=eng#8\">D&amp;C 64:9-1 0</a>) you just bent down and picked up a really big rock that is really heavy and it is only on you when you forgive that person.  It is all about you when you decide to put that rock down. But our perfect example of forgiveness is Christ. When on the cross he set the perfect example of faith and said \"Father forgive them\" in that moment we get the greatest example of forgiveness.  In a way Christ says \"Dad I know what they have done to me and it really hurts but please I don\'t think I could stand it if even one of my brothers doesn\'t have the opportunity to be with me for eternity.\"If Christ, after all that, can still forgive than what can anyone do to us that we can not forgive.</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNow it is <strong>Wednesday</strong>!  lots of work today we contacted a few people and all that fun stuff. Another problem, one of our investigators we went to his \"house\" and he was snorting cocaine, so that was a fun experience.  But we set a return time to come meet with him lol that is our life.\r\n\r\n<strong>Thursday:</strong> as y\'all might have heard I feel off my bike it was pretty bad lol.  It makes it hard to sleep but i am okay. I had to jump up and said because it was a rock that like broke when i was turning i got up and said nice try Satan but the work must go on went to the house to change and clean up then back out into the field and such is life here in Mexico, when ever Satan tries to put us down we just have to get back up.  One thing I think is cool, i wrecked half of my body but nowhere my garments are got hurt at all not a bruise or a scratch just kind of cool.  I am cleaning my wounds with  a yellow bar of soap that is what every one says and then Lorrina, the primary pres, gave me some of this jell stuff it really helps it has marijuana in it, who know it really helps!\r\n<blockquote>spirit time WHY IS THE CHURCH TRUE- Christ gave the parable of the mustard seed in <a href=\"https://www.lds.org/search?q=MATt+13%3a31-32&amp;lang=eng&amp;domains=scriptures\">MAT 13:31-32</a> .  The mustard seed starting as one of the smallest most over-looked seeds turns into a large tree. As we look Joseph Smith was a poor 15 year old boy looked over by many like a mustard seed but as the gospel came forth through him it has grown into the world wide church it is now like a large tree it sure is amazing the way that those things apply to our day. (Garments are a sacred underclothing that members of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints wear.  If you would like to know more about why we wear them here is a link to a <a href=\"https://youtu.be/SkTz_NQqKA8\">great video</a>.)</blockquote>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nits <strong>Friday</strong> I cut open my finger on a fan,  Mexico is killing me slowly. It rained a little today that felt nice. We went to go meet with one of our investigators and he had some friends over, we were like great we can teach more people! They were all drunk and still drinking and offered us beer that was fun lol we set a return appointment.\r\n\r\nits <strong>Saturday</strong> and it was bad like really bad! it hasn\'t stopped raining since last night! we are soaked and no one answered the door we knocked 34 doors today referrals, member, less active and investigator and  not one answered the door.  But such is life out here its hard but we say nope Satan,  we are soaked from head to toe, our bikes are broken, but we are not going to stop, we will keep up the work.\r\nSunday we watched the temple dedication of the Tijuana Mexico Temple.  It was so cool like so so so cool! Knocked 25 doors, one answered, it was good.  They offered us coffee we said no thank you then later their daughter came home andn made some bread toast things and asked if we wanted coffee and the mom was like no they don\'t drink coffee but i think they drink milk and we were like yes mamma we drink milk and then we got some milk hahahahah\r\n<